<p>I have experience that when using widgetVar during the document ready event, I get an undefined object. Below is a sample to show the case:</p>  <blockquote>   <p>$(document).ready(function(){alert(PF('myWidgetVariable'));});</p> </blockquote>  <p>But if I use </p>  <blockquote>   <p>$(window).on('load',function(){alert(PF('myWidgetVariable'));});</p> </blockquote>  <p>I can see there is an object created.</p>  <p>Now the question is, when do exactly primefaces creates the widgets variables?</p>  <p>Is it guaranteed that when the load event is triggered, the widgets variables will be available?</p>